body:
@raghav157 something is incorrect in your dimensions. Your cfg must not be aligned with your data and names file. Follow the directions in this tutorial:
https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3/wiki/Train-Custom-Data
@raghav157 Did you solve the error? I'm facing the same issue.

Yes I have solve it https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3/wiki/Train-Custom-Data
Follow this 
Change filter size in cfg file according to your data classes, which is 255 by default

I met this problem
 "RuntimeError: shape '[512, 256, 3, 3]' is invalid for input of size 1155231"
when I am running
 "python detect.py --cfg cfg/yolov3 --weights/yolo3.weight" 
the sample image is default "zidane.jpg"
and the weight is download from yolo's homepage.
How can i solve it? Thanks very much!
@liqisa Did you solve it?When I ran the train.py,I meet RuntimeError: shape '[128, 256, 1, 1]' is invalid for input of size 18766.It's very similar to your situation.I don't know how to handle it.
@DeepLearning723  Have you solve this problem? I also meet the same question. I have search many pages but no pages tell about this. Can you help me? Thank you very much!

@linjiaquan @DeepLearning723 @liqisa you are receiving these errors because your custom cfg files are not correctly formatted. Read and follow https://github.com/ultralytics/yolov3/wiki/Train-Custom-Data for correct instructions.

@liqisa your command works correctly without issue. It literally can not be any simpler:

```bash
(yolov3) Glenns-iMac:yolov3 glennjocher$ python3 detect.py --cfg cfg/yolov3.cfg --weights weights/yolov3.weights
Namespace(cfg='cfg/yolov3.cfg', conf_thres=0.3, data='data/coco.data', fourcc='mp4v', half=False, images='data/samples', img_size=416, nms_thres=0.5, output='output', webcam=False, weights='weights/yolov3.weights')
Using CPU

image 1/2 data/samples/bus.jpg: 416x320 4 persons, 1 buss, Done. (0.744s)
image 2/2 data/samples/zidane.jpg: 256x416 2 persons, 1 ties, Done. (0.566s)
Results saved to /Users/glennjocher/PycharmProjects/yolov3/output
Done. (1.651s)
```

@allen108108 you always need to specify cfg along with weights:

`python3 detect.py --cfg mycfg --weights --myweights`

Thanks for answering.

I  used yolov3-spp.cfg file and yolov3-spp.weights file but still got the same error........

![2019-11-08](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/48144999/68452495-9ed89780-022d-11ea-87c8-ac22c572ff0f.png)

@allen108108 I'm unable to reproduce your error. I get this. I suggest you git clone a fresh copy and try again, you may have custom changes causing the error.

It seems like you are using Windows BTW. We recommend unix. You can use a Colab instance for free:
https://colab.research.google.com/drive/1G8T-VFxQkjDe4idzN8F-hbIBqkkkQnxw

(yolov3) glennjocher@Glenns-MacBook-Pro yolov3 % python3 detect.py --cfg cfg/yolov3-spp.cfg --weights weights/yolov3-spp.weights --source ./data/samples/zidane.jpg
